Evaluate a candidate run against a baseline using release gate policies.

Exit codes:
  0  pass                   Gate passed; safe to promote.
  1  fail                   Gate failed; regressions detected.
  2  warn                   Soft warning; review before promoting.
  3  insufficient_evidence  Policy could not be evaluated; fix spec or rerun.

This makes the command usable as a CI/CD quality gate.

Usage:
  agentclash compare gate [flags]

Flags:
      --baseline string    Baseline run ID (required)
      --candidate string   Candidate run ID (required)
  -h, --help               help for gate

Global Flags:
      --api-url string     API base URL (overrides config)
      --json               Output in JSON format
      --no-color           Disable color output
      --non-interactive    Disable interactive prompts (also honored: CI=true, AGENTCLASH_NON_INTERACTIVE=1, --json, no TTY)
  -o, --output string      Output format: table, json, yaml
  -q, --quiet              Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose            Enable debug output on stderr
  -w, --workspace string   Workspace ID (overrides config)
      --yes                Skip confirmation prompts
